## What this slice does
Closes the "agent OTel" gap (originally documented in AGENTS.md as not-yet-covered).
These two integrations don't call create_call — they emit OTel GenAI spans that the
trace server ingests via the agent path. OTel set_attribute only accepts scalars,
so nested dicts are illegal; they use IntegrationMetadata.as_otel_attributes()
(flattened: integration.name, integration.version, integration.meta.<k>). The trace
server unflattens dotted keys back into a nested integration dict on ingest
(helpers.unflatten_key_values); "integration" is not a semconv KNOWN_KEY so it lands
in the custom_attrs overflow columns — no server schema change required.

## Injection points
- openai_agents/otel_processor.py: on_span_start is the universal chokepoint (every
  span passes through it). Reuses OPENAI_AGENTS_INTEGRATION from the sibling
  openai_agents.py (slice 3) via the existing import, calling _set_attrs (which
  already skips None/empty).
- claude_agent_sdk/otel_integration.py: no single chokepoint; the flattened attrs
  (_INTEGRATION_OTEL_ATTRS, computed once at module load) are .update()'d into the
  chat_attrs, tool attrs, and turn attrs dicts before they're written to spans.

## Decisions
- Session SDK (weave/session/) intentionally NOT stamped: it's a generic API where
  the user is the integrator; there's no library to attribute. If direct-use
  provenance is ever wanted, add an optional integration arg to start_session/etc.
- First-classing integration.* as queryable semconv columns in
  trace_server/agents/{semconv,schema}.py was considered and deferred — custom_attrs
  storage is sufficient for tracking and avoids a ClickHouse migration.

## Testing
Couldn't import these modules in the base env (need the `agents` and
`claude_agent_sdk` libs). Validated via ruff + ast.parse + manual review. The
as_otel_attributes flattening itself is unit-tested in slice 1.

## Depends on
Slice 1 (as_otel_attributes) and slice 3 (OPENAI_AGENTS_INTEGRATION in openai_agents.py).
